{
  "text": "Theorem 3.1 (M. Gromov [CITATION_1] ). Let (M, g) be a compact Riemannian manifold of dimension n with nonnegative sectional curvature. Then the sum of the Betti numbers of M is bounded by some constant C(n), which depends only on the dimension. K. Grove and K. Shiohama [CITATION_2] have obtained an interesting generalization of the Topological Sphere Theorem. In this result, the upper bound for the sectional curvature is replaced by a lower bound for the diameter. We shall sketch an argument due to M. Berger, which relies on an estimate for the Morse index of geodesics. For a detailed exposition, see [CITATION_3] , Theorem 6.13, or [CITATION_4] , Theorem 1.15. Proposition 3.2. Let (M, g) be a compact Riemannian manifold of dimension n with sectional curvature K \u2265 1. Suppose that p and q are two",
